01:06:30,060 --> 01:06:33,060
In November, last November.

666
01:06:33,060 --> 01:06:35,060
Like November of 19.

667
01:06:35,060 --> 01:06:37,060
November of 19.

668
01:06:37,060 --> 01:06:39,560
And those were in New Zealand too?

669
01:06:39,560 --> 01:06:41,060
New Zealand and Australia.

670
01:06:41,060 --> 01:06:45,060
So New Zealand doesn't have the COVID yet, right?

671
01:06:45,060 --> 01:06:47,060
No, it had it, but it...

672
01:06:47,060 --> 01:06:50,060
It was pretty mild. They were very well controlled.

673
01:06:50,060 --> 01:06:56,560
But we also had Australia. I don't know how things are going in Australia. So we also had sites in Australia.

674
01:06:56,560 --> 01:07:18,060
I mean, I guess it would be an interesting exploration because again, this is one of those things where you now wonder if you repeat the protector study either as it was done with RTB 101 or with RAD 001 or in combination, but you now do it specifically for this virus, do you get a different outcome?

675
01:07:18,560 --> 01:07:21,560
And I do think, you know, we're learning as we get more and more data.

676
01:07:21,560 --> 01:07:28,060
I think we're actually doing a trial in nursing homes now, looking at severity and not just incidents.

677
01:07:28,060 --> 01:07:37,060
Because I think what's happening is once you get infected, you're better able to upregulate that interferon induced innate immune response.

678
01:07:37,060 --> 01:07:41,560
And my guess is that's why you're having less severe symptoms.

679
01:07:41,560 --> 01:07:44,560
It's not happening before you get infected.

680
01:07:44,560 --> 01:07:56,060
I want to make, I think, an important comment because we spend time and Peter, you try to really look at those drugs, apropos mechanisms of COVID-19.

681
01:07:56,060 --> 01:08:04,060
But I think that what we are trying to sell out there is that we are reinforcing...

682
01:08:04,060 --> 01:08:07,060
We're not fighting the virus. We're reinforcing the host.

683
01:08:07,060 --> 01:08:10,060
Okay. We're defending the host.

